# Exercise 5/ Lab 4 - Reusable Barrier Class

This project shows an implementation of a reusable barrier class that employs a custom Semaphore class.  
**Author:** Adam Mcguigan

## Requirements
- Compatible with **Linux** only
- A C++11 compiler (g++ will do fine)
- The MakeFile

## Install
2. Go to Exercises/ directory: cd Exercise Five_Reusable Barriers
3. Build project: make CLEAN && make
4. Run: `./reusable_barrier`

## Project/files Content
- **Barrier:** the barrier implementation, require Semaphore class
- **Sempahore:** implemetation of a Semaphore
- **main.cpp:** the traditional start point of the program, showing off the Barrier implentation

